[2026-02-03 11:03:41:976][007216] FT60X Chip Configuration Programmer

[2026-02-03 11:05:51:805][007216] ----------------------------------------------------------------

[2026-02-03 11:05:51:805][007216] Device Descriptor

[2026-02-03 11:05:51:805][007216] VID: Vendor identification as specified in idVendor field of USB Device Descriptor. This should match the VID in the Windows installation file (INF) used during driver installation.

[2026-02-03 11:05:51:805][007216] PID: Product identification as specified in idProduct field of USB Device Descriptor. This should match the PID in the Windows installation file (INF) used during driver installation.

[2026-02-03 11:05:51:805][007216] ----------------------------------------------------------------

[2026-02-03 11:05:51:805][007216] String Descriptor

[2026-02-03 11:05:51:805][007216] Manufacturer: Name of manufacturer as pointed to by iManufacturer field of USB Device Descriptor. Max of 15 isprintable characters.

[2026-02-03 11:05:51:805][007216] Product description: Description of product as pointed to by iProduct field of USB Device Descriptor. Max of 31 isprintable characters.

[2026-02-03 11:05:51:805][007216] Serial number: Serial number as pointed to by iSerial field of USB Device Descriptor. Max of 15 alphanumeric characters.

[2026-02-03 11:05:51:805][007216] Randomize button will generate a random string of 15 alphanumeric characters.

[2026-02-03 11:05:51:806][007216] ----------------------------------------------------------------

[2026-02-03 11:05:51:806][007216] Configuration Descriptor

[2026-02-03 11:05:51:808][007216] Bus-powered/Self-powered: Self-powered capability of device as specified in bit 6 of bmAttributes field of USB Configuration Descriptor.

[2026-02-03 11:05:51:809][007216] Remote wakeup: Remote wakeup capability of device as specified in bit 5 of bmAttributes field of USB Configuration Descriptor.

[2026-02-03 11:05:51:809][007216] Max power: Maximum power the device can require. It can be deduced from the bMaxPower field of USB Configuration Descriptor. If USB 3, bMaxPower = Max Power / 8. If USB 2, bMaxPower = Max Power / 2.

[2026-02-03 11:05:51:810][007216] ----------------------------------------------------------------

[2026-02-03 11:05:51:810][007216] Data Transfer

[2026-02-03 11:05:51:811][007216] FIFO clock: Speed of FIFO clock in MHz.

[2026-02-03 11:05:51:811][007216] FIFO mode: 245 mode or 600 mode.

[2026-02-03 11:05:51:812][007216] Channel configuration: Number of channels or endpoints in the configuration. A channel contains an OUT and IN endpoint. Note that maximum performance decreases as the number of endpoints increases. To achieve maximum performance, use less endpoints or channels as possible.

[2026-02-03 11:05:51:812][007216] ----------------------------------------------------------------

[2026-02-03 11:05:51:812][007216] Optional Features

[2026-02-03 11:05:51:813][007216] Battery Charging: Enables/disables the detection of power source.

[2026-02-03 11:05:51:813][007216] Battery Charging PIN Cofiguration: Configuration of GPIO pins used for signalling type of power source detected.
Sample setting: 11100100b
	bit7-6=DCP(11)
	bit5-4=CDP(10)
	bit3-2=SDP(01)
	bit1-0=Default(00)
where upper bit is GPIO1 and lower bit is GPIO0.

[2026-02-03 11:05:51:817][007216] Notification Message: Enables/disables sending of notification message for unexpected IN data where there is no existing read requests.
[2026-02-03 11:05:51:817][007216] When this is set on a pipe, host application should not actively read on this pipe, instead will register a callback function. The callback function will be called when there is data available for the pipe.
[2026-02-03 11:05:51:817][007216] This feature is intended for unexpected short packets (maximum of 4kb), such as error status information from the FIFO master to host application.
[2026-02-03 11:05:51:818][007216] For example, for a camera device, user can select 2-channel configuration because it needs 2 IN pipes ? 1 for camera data, 1 for control/error status information. Notification message should be used for the control/error status information pipe but not for the camera data pipe.

[2026-02-03 11:05:51:819][007216] Ignore Session Underrun: Controls the chip behavior when the chip receives less data than expected from FIFO Master.

[2026-02-03 11:05:51:820][007216] When ?On Multiple of MaxPacketSize bytes? is selected, the FIFO master may write in bursts of multiples of MaxPacketSize bytes. When a burst is not a multiple of MaxPacketSize bytes or when the requested length is reached, the session is closed.
[2026-02-03 11:05:51:821][007216] When ?On Multiple of Bus-width bytes? is selected, the FIFO master may write in multiples of bus-width size. When a burst is not a multiple of bus-width size, or the requested length is reached, the session is closed.
[2026-02-03 11:05:51:821][007216] When ?On Multiple of MaxPacketSize bytes? is selected, the device transmits data over the USB in maxPacketSize packets, in parallel, with the FIFO master writes.
[2026-02-03 11:05:51:821][007216] When ?On Multiple of Bus-width bytes? is selected, the device waits for its internal FIFO buffer to be filled completely before initiating a write transfer on the USB.

[2026-02-03 11:05:51:822][007216] Keep Fifo Clock On in Suspend: Option to keep clock on even in suspend state.

[2026-02-03 11:05:51:822][007216] If the master is using the clock from FT600/FT601, and if master needs the clock independent of what state FT600/FT601 is in, then this option can be used.

[2026-02-03 11:05:51:822][007216] Disable Chip Powerdown: Option to Keep Chip powered on even if VBUS not present. Works only when in self-powered.

[2026-02-03 11:05:51:822][007216] 
----------------------------------------------------------------

[2026-02-03 11:05:51:822][007216] Interrupt Latency

[2026-02-03 11:05:51:822][007216] bInterval: Option to modify the interrupt interval.

[2026-02-03 11:05:51:822][007216] Interval is calculated as 2**(bInterval-1) usb frames

[2026-02-03 11:05:51:822][007216] Minimum value is 1 and Max is 16
[2026-02-03 11:05:51:822][007216] 
----------------------------------------------------------------

[2026-02-03 11:05:51:822][007216] Status Information

[2026-02-03 11:05:51:822][007216] Custom Configuration Validity: Indicates whether the configuration data read from the Flash or EEPROM is valid or not. If custom configuration is invalid, firmware will use the default configuration.

[2026-02-03 11:05:51:822][007216] Custom Configuration Checksum: Indicates whether the configuration data is corrupted or not by validating the checksum. If custom configuration checksum is invalid, firmware will use the default configuration.

[2026-02-03 11:05:51:822][007216] GPIO Input: Indicates whether the GPIOs are used as configuration input.
[2026-02-03 11:05:51:822][007216] Note that the GPIOs will only be used as configuration input when device is running default configuration. Below is the pin setting corresponding to mode and channel configuration.
[2026-02-03 11:05:51:822][007216] 	GPIO1 0 ? GPIO0 0 ? 245 mode ? 1 channel
[2026-02-03 11:05:51:822][007216] 	GPIO1 0 ? GPIO0 1 ? 600 mode ? 1 channel
[2026-02-03 11:05:51:822][007216] 	GPIO1 1 ? GPIO0 0 ? 600 mode ? 2 channels
[2026-02-03 11:05:51:822][007216] 	GPIO1 1 ? GPIO0 1 ? 600 mode ? 4 channels

[2026-02-03 11:05:51:822][007216] GPIO 0: Indicates whether GPIO 0 is set to high or low.

[2026-02-03 11:05:51:822][007216] GPIO 1: Indicates whether GPIO 1 is set to high or low.

[2026-02-03 11:05:51:822][007216] Configuration Used: Indicates whether firmware initialized using the custom configuration or default configuration.

